            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>For any presheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> and sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>, there is a natural bijection <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\hom (P, F) \cong  \hom (P^+, F)]]></fr:tex> given by composition with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta _P : P \to  P^+]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><fr:p>As a corollary of this and <fr:link href="algm-001G.xml" title="Iterated plus construction produces a sheaf" addr="algm-001G" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="algm-001G" /></fr:link>, when restricted to separated presheaves, it is left adjoint to the forgetful functor from sheaves to separated presheaves.</fr:p>
  
    
